      <Title GUID="e2e80624-e299-458d-861a-23fa53010ebd">Land</Title>
      <PageElements GUID="9d75a87b-455c-4707-94cb-78d5c1d21517">
        <PageElement GUID="006824c9-1032-476b-8eaf-c44478ffd33c">
          <Graphic GUID="f93308cc-079f-49b4-9b84-af3dc1a420cc"> <![CDATA[<div class="Graphic_Main">
  <img src="Images/c4c60f45-822e-43fd-91e4-c50ffc338937.gif" alt="" align="texttop">
</div>]]></Graphic>
        </PageElement>
        <PageElement GUID="198fe38f-fb16-428d-b220-b4c6128cdf0b">
          <TextBox GUID="7904db6b-8b88-4b7e-b5a6-3a7ca09d9afc"> <![CDATA[<div class="TextBox_Main">
  <Description GUID="078698a1-f4ab-4ea7-a2ad-897380300525">
    <div GUID="43a71cd1-8d65-4bb2-80b8-b07b423f64bf" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Section 9 of the RMA provides that no person may use land in a way that contravenes a rule in a plan unless permitted by a resource consent or unless the activity is an existing use.</div>
    <div GUID="7fcecc45-038f-45f6-9029-8acdcd6cb858" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> </div>
    <div GUID="0bd250a8-e934-43be-9924-d0a4be3a9a20" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">The effect of this provision is generally permissive, i.e. any use is allowed unless it is regulated under a plan. </div>
    <div GUID="2cf5d03c-948c-4831-b1d3-8cd2b16732d5" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> </div>
    <div GUID="6d67875e-a82c-45b9-bfe4-05b7a010500b" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">An important exception is the subdivision of land, which may only be carried out if it has been permitted under the district plan or pursuant to a resource consent. This means that the district plan will dictate what activities do, and what do not, require consent.</div>
    <div GUID="5a460f5b-1425-41ca-abc7-3527ce83e524" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> </div>
    <div GUID="17f8ae46-6cf5-4d1e-90a1-fb62df00a9de" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">The word ‘use’ is defined broadly and includes almost all activities in, on, under or over land. This includes disturbance to the habitats of plants (i.e. tree clearance) and animals and the alteration, removal and demolition of any structure or building. </div>
    <div GUID="4971c529-3c7a-4f2f-b3be-6dd10e147ad9" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> </div>
    <div GUID="3d551e10-962a-420e-95db-5734dddb5623" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">‘Land’ is defined to include the surface of water in any lake or river. However it doesn’t extend to lake or river beds or land in the coastal marine area (foreshore/seabed) which are dealt with separately under the RMA.</div>
  </Description>
</div>]]></TextBox>
        </PageElement>
      </PageElements>
    </Page>
    <Page ID="Page5" IsActive="true" GUID="0deeb198-1e74-472e-851f-e7d2ceea05f9">
      <IncludedInTOC GUID="b541e30d-683d-4c9d-b9c2-73671f6747ec">true</IncludedInTOC>
      <Title GUID="6e049f6a-fd79-41d2-86e9-64979a1bae58">Water</Title>
      <PageElements GUID="830da2fe-8154-4fcc-8336-096fed3db188">
        <PageElement GUID="a3c25f4a-dde0-46e3-a3e0-3a81040bebad">
          <Graphic GUID="1fde0f87-c622-4e50-91b4-a622e4fbdd3f"> <![CDATA[<div class="Graphic_Main">
  <img src="Images/8b668890-e2eb-46a8-a83b-c744b7f3f1c8.gif" alt="" align="texttop">
</div>]]></Graphic>
        </PageElement>
        <PageElement GUID="7b7677e3-a7b4-4f05-9b9b-2a0ba86cb464">
          <TextBox GUID="ac228e16-6bd5-4830-92fa-3b6987d84eed"> <![CDATA[<div class="TextBox_Main">
  <Description GUID="f66334cc-1bf5-465a-b90e-8dbf568dfe2d">
    <div GUID="b7a0131f-466d-45cc-98c7-9aabb65adb17" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Section 14 of the RMA provides that no person is able to take, use, dam or divert any water unless allowed by a rule in the plan or pursuant to a resource consent. The provisions of the regional plan will dictate what consents are required for these activities.</div>
    <div GUID="e9500337-9eb9-4b0a-8f16-d57998af4837" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> </div>
    <div GUID="6446b08b-4ae5-4b32-b6b0-94c1c95c8d30" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">‘Water’ includes any heat or energy from water and sources of geothermal energy (with limited exceptions).</div>
    <div GUID="e2946d9c-ff1a-4128-abf1-7947a9e77fda" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> </div>
    <div GUID="c5b42162-da68-456c-8d88-35a9dfe140f0" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">If water is taken or used for an individual’s reasonable domestic needs, or the needs of animals, then this is permitted as long as there are no possible adverse effects on the environment.</div>
    <div GUID="2887d73b-ef8b-4928-995e-203028d8a8d7" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> </div>
    <div GUID="ccb8196d-50ee-48b8-b5db-aa63d9a0d314" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Note that this exception does not apply to open coastal water.</div>
  </Description>
</div>]]></TextBox>
        </PageElement>
      </PageElements>
    </Page>
